1
00:01:01,437 --> 00:01:03,522
EPISODE 11

2
00:01:03,606 --> 00:01:06,066
- You're getting off work late, huh?
- I have a shoot tomorrow.

3
00:01:06,150 --> 00:01:07,735
So I wanted to get ready.

4
00:01:13,949 --> 00:01:15,659
- Um, ma'am.
- What?

5
00:01:15,743 --> 00:01:17,119
When do you have a moment?

6
00:01:17,203 --> 00:01:18,370
Why do you ask?

7
00:01:18,454 --> 00:01:20,247
It might be a good time
for some new headshots.

8
00:01:20,331 --> 00:01:22,500
You've been getting
a lot of media coverage lately.

9
00:01:22,583 --> 00:01:24,835
We could talk about that later. Not now.

10
00:01:31,842 --> 00:01:33,969
- [alarm blaring]
- [device buzzes]

11
00:01:34,053 --> 00:01:35,805
[Seol-ah] <i>The exit code is different.</i>

12
00:01:49,276 --> 00:01:50,778
[beeping]

13
00:01:50,861 --> 00:01:52,321
[buzzes]

14
00:01:55,282 --> 00:01:56,325
[buzzes]

15
00:01:59,036 --> 00:02:00,454
[door unlocks]

16
00:02:06,252 --> 00:02:08,087
[breathes heavily]

17
00:02:09,964 --> 00:02:11,674
Seol-ah. Seol-ah!

18
00:02:13,300 --> 00:02:14,343
We have to go.

19
00:04:01,700 --> 00:04:04,912
Oh, yes. This is where it belongs.

20
00:04:16,715 --> 00:04:18,050
- Let's go.
- Okay.

21
00:04:24,598 --> 00:04:27,434
[line ringing]

22
00:04:28,560 --> 00:04:30,980
Hey, when will you be wrapping up?

23
00:04:31,981 --> 00:04:33,399
Well, you better hurry up.

24
00:04:34,191 --> 00:04:37,611
We have to finish
before the police end up finding them.

25
00:04:38,404 --> 00:04:39,405
Are you okay?

26
00:04:41,490 --> 00:04:45,035
The things you were looking for,
were they in there?

27
00:04:46,412 --> 00:04:47,621
Yes, they are.

28
00:04:48,288 --> 00:04:51,625
Taemyung's art, the ones
Chair Kim swapped out,

29
00:04:53,002 --> 00:04:54,628
and my dad's painting too.

30
00:04:57,256 --> 00:05:00,676
Everything burned up,
every single photo included.

31
00:05:00,759 --> 00:05:02,636
But my family's last memories

32
00:05:03,679 --> 00:05:05,347
are still trapped in there

33
00:05:06,598 --> 00:05:07,850
[sighs]

34
00:05:07,933 --> 00:05:10,769
I will never forgive Chair Kim for this.

35
00:05:12,104 --> 00:05:14,064
I promise I'll make her pay.

36
00:05:15,441 --> 00:05:16,442
I'm with you

37
00:05:17,651 --> 00:05:19,278
whatever you decide.

38
00:05:42,092 --> 00:05:43,218
Have a good time.

39
00:06:00,444 --> 00:06:02,446
[attendees chattering]

40
00:06:08,410 --> 00:06:09,995
Everything's ready, right?

41
00:06:12,664 --> 00:06:15,501
[chattering continues]

42
00:06:41,443 --> 00:06:42,903
SEARCH AND SEIZURE WARRANT
ARREST WARRANT

43
00:06:58,168 --> 00:07:00,087
"Untitled" by Lee Soo-dam.

44
00:07:00,170 --> 00:07:03,006
Sold to a bidder in the room for $270,000.

45
00:07:03,090 --> 00:07:04,716
Congratulations.

46
00:07:14,726 --> 00:07:18,605
This unpublished major work
believed to be the last painting

47
00:07:18,689 --> 00:07:21,567
completed by the late artist Song Hwan-ju,

48
00:07:21,650 --> 00:07:24,361
estimated at over $4.6 million

49
00:07:24,444 --> 00:07:27,906
is expected to surpass
their most famous work, Cheong-myeong.

50
00:07:33,162 --> 00:07:38,417
However, today this artwork
will not be going up for auction.

51
00:07:38,500 --> 00:07:40,335
[audience murmuring]

52
00:07:43,088 --> 00:07:45,132
Because it's not an authentic piece!

53
00:07:49,428 --> 00:07:52,973
This piece was consigned
through unofficial channels…

54
00:07:53,056 --> 00:07:54,224
What's she saying?

55
00:07:54,308 --> 00:07:56,101
…at the direction
of Royal Auction Chair Kim Sun-ae.

56
00:07:56,810 --> 00:08:00,772
The piece was submitted for appraisal,
since I questioned its authenticity,

57
00:08:00,856 --> 00:08:02,608
- and the analysis revealed…
- What is she doing?

58
00:08:02,691 --> 00:08:03,692
- …that the adhesive used…
- Hey.

59
00:08:03,775 --> 00:08:06,653
- What the hell are you doing, Ms. Han?
- …was an industrial synthetic resin

60
00:08:06,737 --> 00:08:10,449
rather than the natural glue that
artist Song Hwan-ju insisted on using.

61
00:08:10,532 --> 00:08:12,201
ART AUTHENTICATION REPORT: FORGERY

62
00:08:12,284 --> 00:08:13,452
[sirens blaring]

63
00:08:23,086 --> 00:08:25,005
[Seol-ah] <i>Even the signature is different.</i>

64
00:08:25,088 --> 00:08:26,715
SIGNATURE COMPARISON ANALYSIS
FORGERY - GENUINE

65
00:08:26,798 --> 00:08:28,550
The character for "Hwan" in his name

66
00:08:28,634 --> 00:08:30,510
is written incorrectly,
using the "child" radical

67
00:08:30,594 --> 00:08:32,387
instead of the correct "fire" radical.

68
00:08:32,471 --> 00:08:33,722
[in Spanish] You idiot!

69
00:08:33,805 --> 00:08:36,934
[Seol-ah, in English] Therefore,
the appraisal agency has determined

70
00:08:37,017 --> 00:08:40,479
that this piece is clearly
a forged artwork.

71
00:08:40,562 --> 00:08:42,105
Get her. Drag her down. Okay?

72
00:08:42,189 --> 00:08:43,941
Yes, ma'am. That crazy little…

73
00:08:54,493 --> 00:08:55,994
We have evidence that the works

74
00:08:56,078 --> 00:09:00,916
the Taemyung Cultural Foundation recently
lost in the fire were also forgeries.

75
00:09:00,999 --> 00:09:03,335
Hey! Drag her out!

76
00:09:03,418 --> 00:09:05,921
[Mr. Song] Shit. No photos. No photos!

77
00:09:06,004 --> 00:09:08,757
[Seol-ah] So, where is the real one then?

78
00:09:12,636 --> 00:09:14,054
[audience gasps]

79
00:09:14,137 --> 00:09:16,682
- No way.
- There's the real one.

80
00:09:16,765 --> 00:09:20,185
[Seol-ah] As you can see, she moved them
to her secret storage vault.

81
00:09:20,269 --> 00:09:22,646
Inside is her collection,

82
00:09:22,729 --> 00:09:27,734
all of which was gathered
through embezzlement, theft, and swapping.

83
00:09:27,818 --> 00:09:29,861
[screams]

84
00:09:29,945 --> 00:09:31,488
[reporter 1] How did you get this footage?

85
00:09:31,571 --> 00:09:34,032
[reporter 2] When did you start planning
to blow the whistle on her?

86
00:09:34,116 --> 00:09:35,117
Ma'am!

87
00:09:35,200 --> 00:09:38,120
Is there more evidence that
this was Chair Kim Sun-ae's doing?

88
00:09:41,999 --> 00:09:44,293
Artist Han Jin-woo, who painted this work,

89
00:09:44,376 --> 00:09:46,712
was once celebrated
as a genius in the art world,

90
00:09:46,795 --> 00:09:49,965
then was reduced to a mere forger
by Chair Kim.

91
00:09:52,009 --> 00:09:54,803
I'd like to take this opportunity

92
00:09:55,762 --> 00:09:59,683
to restore the honor of the artist
who died under a cloud of disgrace.

93
00:10:00,309 --> 00:10:04,229
Even at this very moment,
another forgery orchestrated by Chair Kim

94
00:10:04,313 --> 00:10:06,231
is likely being created somewhere.

95
00:10:07,024 --> 00:10:10,402
I therefore request that
the police investigate this thoroughly.

96
00:10:10,485 --> 00:10:12,821
[dramatic music plays]

97
00:10:19,119 --> 00:10:24,082
Hey, do you think people would actually
believe that doctored footage?

98
00:10:24,166 --> 00:10:25,834
- [door opens]
- [people gasping]

99
00:10:29,546 --> 00:10:30,797
Ms. Kim Sun-ae.

100
00:10:31,465 --> 00:10:33,633
You're under arrest
for embezzlement and fraud,

101
00:10:33,717 --> 00:10:36,261
and for violating
the Criminal Proceeds Act.

102
00:10:37,846 --> 00:10:39,806
At least the police seem to believe it.

103
00:10:39,890 --> 00:10:41,475
- Ma'am, ma'am…
- Let go.

104
00:10:41,558 --> 00:10:45,479
I did nothing wrong. How dare you…
You guys are making a mistake!

105
00:11:01,870 --> 00:11:02,871
[sighs]

106
00:11:02,954 --> 00:11:03,955
What is all this?

107
00:11:04,456 --> 00:11:06,792
[Eun-gyeom] Wow, is this supposed
to be an art gallery?

108
00:11:07,584 --> 00:11:09,086
How much money did she pocket this way?

109
00:11:18,678 --> 00:11:21,014
[Gong] We've secured
all the evidence from your office.

110
00:11:21,098 --> 00:11:22,182
What?

111
00:11:22,265 --> 00:11:25,977
Who do you people think you are,
going into my office, huh?

112
00:11:26,603 --> 00:11:30,107
Don't touch anything!
Don't touch anything! It's all mine!

113
00:11:30,941 --> 00:11:33,652
Don't touch anything!
Do not touch anything.

114
00:11:33,735 --> 00:11:35,779
- They're all mine! Don't touch anything.
- Come on!

115
00:11:35,862 --> 00:11:37,489
Hey, Han Seol-ah!

116
00:11:38,073 --> 00:11:40,992
Hey! Han Seol-ah!

117
00:11:44,871 --> 00:11:45,956
Let go!

118
00:11:47,040 --> 00:11:48,333
Han Seol-ah!

119
00:12:13,483 --> 00:12:16,486
They'll install locking devices
and restrict access.

120
00:12:17,154 --> 00:12:19,114
Since there are so many high-value works,

121
00:12:19,906 --> 00:12:23,618
the vault will be sealed until they can
be moved to a separate location.

122
00:12:24,786 --> 00:12:27,706
We need to cross-check the evidence that
you submitted.

123
00:12:28,331 --> 00:12:32,210
Could you verify them
before the expert appraisal?

124
00:12:34,880 --> 00:12:37,424
You won't find this painting on the list.

125
00:12:37,507 --> 00:12:41,136
The original artist is Han Jin-woo.
He was my father.

126
00:12:44,264 --> 00:12:45,807
It can be returned, right?

127
00:12:46,808 --> 00:12:49,853
- Make sure Seol-ah can get it back.
- Okay.

128
00:13:00,572 --> 00:13:01,698
[Woo-seok] What is this?

129
00:13:01,781 --> 00:13:03,283
It hasn't been unwrapped yet.

130
00:13:07,245 --> 00:13:08,246
[gasps]

131
00:13:12,501 --> 00:13:13,502
The Stiller.

132
00:13:14,669 --> 00:13:16,546
The painting worth over $10 million?

133
00:13:18,590 --> 00:13:20,425
No way. She swapped this one too?

134
00:13:21,218 --> 00:13:23,929
It's the authentic Stiller piece
from the exhibition hall.

135
00:13:25,180 --> 00:13:28,225
Does that mean
she's making a forgery of this too?

136
00:13:29,142 --> 00:13:30,602
[tense music plays]

137
00:13:41,363 --> 00:13:42,822
- Woo-seok, wait.
- I'll call you.

138
00:14:04,886 --> 00:14:06,680
[line ringing]

139
00:14:06,763 --> 00:14:08,390
You're still at the auction house?

140
00:14:08,890 --> 00:14:10,016
Do you have a minute?

141
00:14:12,435 --> 00:14:14,229
Get everyone to leave the worksite.

142
00:14:14,312 --> 00:14:16,648
[sighs] I'll do the cleanup.
Just leave now!

143
00:14:17,482 --> 00:14:19,484
Do as I say, you idiots!

144
00:14:20,569 --> 00:14:21,570
Shit.

145
00:15:31,640 --> 00:15:33,308
[door opens]

146
00:15:34,184 --> 00:15:35,602
The hell?

147
00:15:35,685 --> 00:15:37,520
You guys still haven't left?

148
00:15:44,444 --> 00:15:45,570
Who's there?

149
00:15:58,500 --> 00:16:01,503
It's been a while, Ju Hyun-su.

150
00:16:01,586 --> 00:16:03,171
[sighs] Shit…

151
00:16:04,005 --> 00:16:06,257
You were the investigator
in the Taemyung case?

152
00:16:06,341 --> 00:16:08,385
You can't run anymore, you bastard.

153
00:16:08,468 --> 00:16:10,637
Get ready to rot in prison.

154
00:16:10,720 --> 00:16:13,306
I can just burn everything
and I'll be fine.

155
00:16:14,766 --> 00:16:16,476
Do you want to die too, you bastard?

156
00:16:20,313 --> 00:16:21,648
Goddamn it…

157
00:16:21,731 --> 00:16:23,525
You just confessed, didn't you?

158
00:16:23,608 --> 00:16:25,443
- Shit…
- That you killed Woo-hee!

159
00:16:25,527 --> 00:16:28,071
My life got screwed up
after meeting that bitch!

160
00:16:28,154 --> 00:16:30,532
If I knew her brother was a cop,
I wouldn't have touched her.

161
00:16:30,615 --> 00:16:32,575
Shut your mouth, you bastard!

162
00:16:32,659 --> 00:16:35,161
[laughs] She was crazy about me.

163
00:16:35,245 --> 00:16:37,497
She begged me to take her in that truck.

164
00:16:37,580 --> 00:16:40,542
That girl was so starved for affection.

165
00:16:40,625 --> 00:16:43,211
- [laughs]
- I said shut up, you son of a bitch!

166
00:16:43,294 --> 00:16:44,796
[Woo-seok screams]

167
00:16:47,549 --> 00:16:49,175
[grunts]

168
00:16:52,095 --> 00:16:54,139
[shouting]

169
00:16:56,683 --> 00:16:58,601
[breathes heavily]

170
00:16:58,685 --> 00:16:59,686
Come here.

171
00:17:07,610 --> 00:17:10,739
She was so young
but she didn't want to be a burden

172
00:17:10,822 --> 00:17:13,825
to her big brother. Did you know that?

173
00:17:14,951 --> 00:17:17,829
That bitch's death, it's all your fault.

174
00:17:18,413 --> 00:17:19,831
No.

175
00:17:19,914 --> 00:17:22,792
No! No! No!

176
00:17:22,876 --> 00:17:25,670
No. You son of a bitch!

177
00:17:25,754 --> 00:17:27,422
- Die, you bastard!
- [Seol-ah] Hey, grab him!

178
00:17:27,505 --> 00:17:28,715
- [Gong] Woo-seok, stop!
- Die!

179
00:17:28,798 --> 00:17:30,300
[Woo-seok shouting]

180
00:17:30,383 --> 00:17:32,093
- Stop!
- [Gong] Stop! Stop it.

181
00:17:32,177 --> 00:17:35,764
- Woo-seok, stop. Stop, that's enough.
- [Gong] Hey!

182
00:17:35,847 --> 00:17:37,307
Please.

183
00:17:40,518 --> 00:17:42,270
- Hey.
- [grunts]

184
00:17:48,401 --> 00:17:49,486
[Gong] Come on!

185
00:18:05,460 --> 00:18:06,461
[breathing heavily]

186
00:18:18,014 --> 00:18:19,390
Hey, it's all over now.

187
00:18:21,059 --> 00:18:22,435
You can relax.

188
00:18:25,063 --> 00:18:27,106
[sobbing]

189
00:18:28,817 --> 00:18:30,902
[gentle music plays]

190
00:18:30,985 --> 00:18:32,153
It was me…

191
00:18:34,364 --> 00:18:36,825
I'm the one who made Woo-hee like that.

192
00:18:37,992 --> 00:18:39,160
It was me.

193
00:18:40,078 --> 00:18:41,830
[sobbing continues]

194
00:18:43,122 --> 00:18:44,749
You said the same thing to me too,

195
00:18:46,209 --> 00:18:48,002
that it wasn't my fault.

196
00:18:48,086 --> 00:18:51,172
And now, I'll return those words to you.

197
00:18:52,465 --> 00:18:54,175
It's not your fault, Woo-seok.

198
00:18:54,926 --> 00:18:56,386
You always did your best.

199
00:18:57,095 --> 00:18:58,763
Let me say that back to you.

200
00:19:24,163 --> 00:19:25,456
[Gong] Ah, geez.

201
00:19:27,709 --> 00:19:28,960
[sighs]

202
00:19:43,474 --> 00:19:45,351
[Woo-hee] <i>Please don't get hurt.</i>

203
00:19:47,687 --> 00:19:51,065
<i>You know you're all I have, brother.</i>

204
00:20:03,953 --> 00:20:05,204
[chuckles]

205
00:20:06,831 --> 00:20:07,957
[chuckles]

206
00:20:16,633 --> 00:20:19,427
[Hyun-su] <i>That bitch's death.</i>
<i>It's all your fault.</i>

207
00:20:28,519 --> 00:20:29,520
[sighs]

208
00:20:34,484 --> 00:20:36,736
[Gong] Your name. I know it's Ju Hyun-su.

209
00:20:36,819 --> 00:20:37,904
STATEMENT

210
00:20:38,488 --> 00:20:39,489
Your date of birth.

211
00:20:43,451 --> 00:20:46,955
Hey. Think you can pull
that right to remain silent crap? Geez.

212
00:20:47,038 --> 00:20:48,247
[sighs]

213
00:20:51,876 --> 00:20:55,630
- What the hell…
- This is the file on the Cha Woo-hee case.

214
00:20:55,713 --> 00:20:58,758
I couldn't throw it away
for six whole years.

215
00:20:59,676 --> 00:21:01,594
When Woo-seok was
practically spitting blood,

216
00:21:02,220 --> 00:21:03,513
saying you killed his sister,

217
00:21:04,097 --> 00:21:06,683
I laughed in his face.
I told him he was just being emotional.

218
00:21:07,433 --> 00:21:10,937
You already killed someone once,
so you expect us to believe you now?

219
00:21:12,230 --> 00:21:13,982
Start talking, you bastard!

220
00:21:14,065 --> 00:21:16,734
How far did Chair Kim go?
You killed Paek Jun-beom, right?

221
00:21:16,818 --> 00:21:19,028
No! I didn't kill Paek Jun-beom!

222
00:21:20,321 --> 00:21:21,489
Then who did you kill?

223
00:21:22,782 --> 00:21:24,117
Did you kill Cha Woo-hee?

224
00:21:26,452 --> 00:21:28,246
Did you kill Kim Yun-ji?

225
00:21:29,038 --> 00:21:31,499
[sighs] Shit…

226
00:21:46,014 --> 00:21:47,432
What is all this?

227
00:21:48,433 --> 00:21:49,976
I wanted to prepare you something.

228
00:21:50,059 --> 00:21:51,936
Oh, no. I'm fine. Thanks.

229
00:21:52,020 --> 00:21:54,772
I-I mean, it must be hard for you
to use fire.

230
00:21:54,856 --> 00:21:57,066
It's an induction stove,
I think I can handle it.

231
00:21:57,859 --> 00:21:59,777
[exhales heavily] But you don't have to.

232
00:22:00,695 --> 00:22:02,363
- Uh… Should I wash this first?
- Uh…

233
00:22:04,323 --> 00:22:08,202
Go inside and get some rest.
You've already been through a lot.

234
00:22:16,002 --> 00:22:18,921
You know, I'm not very good at cooking.

235
00:22:20,298 --> 00:22:23,301
Especially when someone is watching me.

236
00:22:30,725 --> 00:22:31,726
[chuckles]

237
00:22:40,610 --> 00:22:41,819
CARROT

238
00:22:43,821 --> 00:22:44,947
GREEN ONION

239
00:22:57,001 --> 00:22:58,419
ADD THE BEEF

240
00:23:21,275 --> 00:23:22,860
I can't promise it'll taste good.

241
00:23:25,571 --> 00:23:27,615
This was my first time making porridge.

242
00:23:32,120 --> 00:23:35,540
I just thought it'd be easier to eat
than plain rice.

243
00:23:38,751 --> 00:23:39,752
Thank you.

244
00:23:42,588 --> 00:23:43,631
It looks great.

245
00:24:04,944 --> 00:24:06,195
Delicious.

246
00:24:14,120 --> 00:24:18,749
I often thought about the meal
you made for me.

247
00:24:19,542 --> 00:24:21,252
After the police interrogation,

248
00:24:21,335 --> 00:24:24,088
when I broke physically and mentally.

249
00:24:25,506 --> 00:24:30,553
That warm bowl of rice you made
helped me get back on my feet again.

250
00:24:33,931 --> 00:24:35,850
But you didn't wanna see me anymore.

251
00:24:36,851 --> 00:24:38,186
I was afraid…

252
00:24:40,980 --> 00:24:45,443
that something might happen to you
if you stayed by my side.

253
00:24:48,905 --> 00:24:50,323
And how about now?

254
00:24:52,533 --> 00:24:54,285
I'm still scared, even now.

255
00:24:56,245 --> 00:24:59,081
But I… I will give it a try.

256
00:25:00,666 --> 00:25:02,376
You are the one who taught me that.

257
00:25:03,044 --> 00:25:06,839
You told me not to run away
or to push you away,

258
00:25:08,424 --> 00:25:10,801
to stay by your side and keep you safe.

259
00:25:13,763 --> 00:25:17,725
I think now I understand
about how you're feeling.

260
00:25:20,978 --> 00:25:21,979
But

261
00:25:23,231 --> 00:25:24,815
we have to keep going.

262
00:25:27,693 --> 00:25:29,987
I cant promise that
things will get better,

263
00:25:31,739 --> 00:25:32,740
because

264
00:25:34,158 --> 00:25:36,786
we'll carry this pain
for the rest of our lives.

265
00:25:40,122 --> 00:25:42,250
Let's get through it together.

266
00:25:44,877 --> 00:25:45,962
[gulps]

267
00:25:55,221 --> 00:25:56,222
Hurry up and eat.

268
00:25:58,266 --> 00:25:59,392
It's really good.

269
00:26:01,352 --> 00:26:02,395
[chuckles]

270
00:26:09,527 --> 00:26:10,903
[sniffles]

271
00:26:28,838 --> 00:26:31,132
We analyzed Chair Kim's computer

272
00:26:31,215 --> 00:26:34,260
and found chats with Kim Yun-ji
on the company messenger.

273
00:26:34,844 --> 00:26:36,345
I think you should take a look at them.

274
00:26:36,429 --> 00:26:37,596
ASSOCIATE AUCTIONEER KIM YUN-JI

275
00:26:38,264 --> 00:26:39,807
[Ms. Kim] <i>The painting my father bought,</i>

276
00:26:39,890 --> 00:26:42,601
<i>you personally brought it in</i>
<i>from New York, right?</i>

277
00:26:42,685 --> 00:26:44,186
[Chair Kim] <i>Why do you ask?</i>

278
00:26:44,270 --> 00:26:46,105
[Ms. Kim] <i>Isn't this</i>
<i>completely crossing the line?</i>

279
00:26:46,188 --> 00:26:48,941
<i>I introduced that painting to my family</i>
<i>in good faith.</i>

280
00:26:49,734 --> 00:26:52,320
[Chair Kim] <i>Come up. Let's talk in person.</i>

281
00:26:54,739 --> 00:26:55,948
[Ms. Kim] Funny, isn't it?

282
00:26:56,032 --> 00:27:00,202
The head of the Tax Investigation Bureau
has a daughter who's an auctioneer,

283
00:27:00,286 --> 00:27:02,246
yet there's a forgery in his house.

284
00:27:02,330 --> 00:27:04,790
What kind of nonsense are you saying?

285
00:27:05,416 --> 00:27:08,753
I had two outside appraisals done,
and the results are the same.

286
00:27:09,378 --> 00:27:13,507
If my dad finds out,
what do you think will happen?

287
00:27:14,091 --> 00:27:16,010
Are you threatening me right now?

288
00:27:16,886 --> 00:27:19,305
I'm saying we should try to sort this out.

289
00:27:19,805 --> 00:27:20,973
What is it you want?

290
00:27:22,391 --> 00:27:23,559
The main auction podium.

291
00:27:24,226 --> 00:27:25,394
[scoffs]

292
00:27:27,229 --> 00:27:29,231
You want me to get rid of Ms. Han?

293
00:27:30,441 --> 00:27:33,277
This must've put
a lot of pressure on Chair Kim.

294
00:27:33,778 --> 00:27:35,946
She already had plenty to worry about.

295
00:27:36,030 --> 00:27:38,532
I thought it could be a motive
for Kim Yun-ji's murder.

296
00:27:45,873 --> 00:27:48,626
[Seong-il] Taemyung's paintings
that supposedly burned in the fire

297
00:27:48,709 --> 00:27:51,087
were found in your secret vault,
and you know nothing about it?

298
00:27:52,546 --> 00:27:56,300
My client was simply storing the paintings
at the customer's request.

299
00:27:56,384 --> 00:28:00,346
This is a matter of Taemyung's negligence
and an insurance issue,

300
00:28:00,429 --> 00:28:02,473
not a crime committed by my client.

301
00:28:04,392 --> 00:28:05,976
Then let's talk about this.

302
00:28:06,602 --> 00:28:09,230
That Stiller painting
worth over six million dollars.

303
00:28:09,730 --> 00:28:12,483
You just happened to swoop in
when the owner died, didn't you?

304
00:28:13,442 --> 00:28:15,903
[gulps, clears throat] The same goes here.

305
00:28:17,029 --> 00:28:20,449
My client simply kept the artwork
in the vault

306
00:28:20,533 --> 00:28:23,035
until the inheritance process
was finalized.

307
00:28:23,869 --> 00:28:25,496
That's standard practice.

308
00:28:25,579 --> 00:28:28,040
But then why did you make a forgery?

309
00:28:30,042 --> 00:28:31,419
Why all that trouble?

310
00:28:32,837 --> 00:28:36,257
Your lackey, Ju Hyun-su, has been caught.

311
00:28:37,049 --> 00:28:39,385
[moody music plays]

312
00:28:39,468 --> 00:28:43,431
There is no point in keeping this up,
Ms. Kim Sun-ae.

313
00:28:43,514 --> 00:28:44,515
[sighs]

314
00:28:45,349 --> 00:28:47,017
The way you speak

315
00:28:47,726 --> 00:28:49,353
is very rude.

316
00:28:50,146 --> 00:28:54,650
Mr. Detective, do you even have an idea
of who I am?

317
00:28:55,901 --> 00:29:00,114
Well, the mistake's already been made
and can't be undone.

318
00:29:00,781 --> 00:29:06,328
Whether your career as a cop goes down
a flower path or a thorny one

319
00:29:06,871 --> 00:29:08,914
depends on this moment.

320
00:29:09,748 --> 00:29:11,125
Can't you feel that?

321
00:29:11,208 --> 00:29:12,960
You should be worrying about yourself.

322
00:29:13,878 --> 00:29:17,590
Insurance fraud, embezzlement,
selling forgeries,

323
00:29:17,673 --> 00:29:21,093
and even incitement to murder.

324
00:29:27,057 --> 00:29:29,268
You have a lot of nerve, you know?

325
00:29:30,186 --> 00:29:33,981
How ungrateful can you be
to stab Chair Kim in the back?

326
00:29:35,399 --> 00:29:37,359
What exactly are you really after?

327
00:29:37,443 --> 00:29:39,904
Are you trying to become CEO
while she's away?

328
00:29:40,654 --> 00:29:42,656
That's probably what you are after.

329
00:29:43,365 --> 00:29:45,576
Who do you think
you're slandering right now?

330
00:29:45,659 --> 00:29:46,660
Hey.

331
00:29:47,369 --> 00:29:48,496
You think I'm you?

332
00:29:49,747 --> 00:29:53,751
I'm just doing what I can
to sort things out from my position.

333
00:29:54,502 --> 00:29:57,546
I should own what I started.

334
00:30:00,216 --> 00:30:01,217
[scoffs]

335
00:30:01,884 --> 00:30:02,885
Fine.

336
00:30:03,385 --> 00:30:05,721
I don't know how long it'll last,
but good luck.

337
00:30:06,347 --> 00:30:07,973
Chair Kim will be out soon.

338
00:30:09,517 --> 00:30:10,559
[Tae-seok sighs]

339
00:30:11,685 --> 00:30:13,979
Our upcoming auctions will probably
fall through, won't they?

340
00:30:14,063 --> 00:30:16,398
We've already had
this many client complaints.

341
00:30:16,982 --> 00:30:18,609
Most are canceling consignments.

342
00:30:18,692 --> 00:30:20,486
[grunts] So annoying.

343
00:30:20,569 --> 00:30:23,155
[Seol-ah] Give me the list.
I'll call them myself

344
00:30:23,239 --> 00:30:24,907
and try to convince them to stay.

345
00:30:24,990 --> 00:30:27,993
Ms. Han, you came to work?

346
00:30:28,077 --> 00:30:29,370
Are you all right?

347
00:30:29,995 --> 00:30:31,997
I owe you all an apology.

348
00:30:32,081 --> 00:30:36,168
I know better than anyone
how much you all love Royal Auction,

349
00:30:36,252 --> 00:30:37,670
yet I caused all of this.

350
00:30:37,753 --> 00:30:40,047
That's why I'm really sorry.

351
00:30:40,881 --> 00:30:43,050
Gosh, no. You did the right thing.

352
00:30:44,969 --> 00:30:47,555
Honestly, we all think it's for the best.

353
00:30:48,097 --> 00:30:51,100
We were unknowingly participating
in Chair Kim's fraud,

354
00:30:51,183 --> 00:30:52,560
so it's actually a relief.

355
00:30:56,647 --> 00:30:58,315
Ma'am remember you put your trust in us…

356
00:30:58,399 --> 00:31:00,359
[client 1] <i>They talked about</i>
<i>forgeries and embezzlement,</i>

357
00:31:00,442 --> 00:31:01,443
<i>how can I believe you?</i>

358
00:31:01,527 --> 00:31:03,279
So we will take full responsibility
for every--

359
00:31:03,362 --> 00:31:05,990
<i>Do you think I'd be okay with it?</i>
<i>Send my paintings back right now!</i>

360
00:31:06,073 --> 00:31:07,449
I promise that I will visit you--

361
00:31:07,533 --> 00:31:10,452
<i>I don't care about compensation.</i>
<i>I'm done doing business with you!</i>

362
00:31:10,536 --> 00:31:11,537
[line clicks]

363
00:31:20,170 --> 00:31:22,339
- [knocks on door]
- [door opens]

364
00:31:24,216 --> 00:31:25,968
Um, Ms. Han.

365
00:31:26,802 --> 00:31:31,056
Artist Han Jin-woo, he's your, uh,
family, isn't he?

366
00:31:32,933 --> 00:31:35,436
Mm-hmm. He's my father.

367
00:31:36,979 --> 00:31:39,982
I had no idea you were going
through so much pain.

368
00:31:40,899 --> 00:31:43,986
I'm sorry that I couldn't be there
for you more.

369
00:31:44,570 --> 00:31:45,821
Thank you.

370
00:31:45,904 --> 00:31:48,407
I really appreciate the warm welcome.

371
00:31:48,490 --> 00:31:49,992
I thought I'd be chewed out.

372
00:31:50,618 --> 00:31:53,954
It must've been so hard for you.

373
00:31:55,080 --> 00:31:57,499
Things will get harder for all of us.

374
00:31:57,583 --> 00:32:01,295
I'll do anything.
I'm ready for what's coming.

375
00:32:12,598 --> 00:32:17,436
I thought only Cha Woo-seok was sincere,
but Han Seol-ah is sincere too.

376
00:32:18,729 --> 00:32:21,482
[sighs] Yeesh, it makes my head spin.

377
00:32:21,565 --> 00:32:24,401
I can't imagine
what would have happened to you…

378
00:32:24,485 --> 00:32:27,696
I had to make him pay for what he did.

379
00:32:29,073 --> 00:32:31,367
Captain's even angrier than I am.

380
00:32:31,450 --> 00:32:33,494
I think he feels so guilty towards you.

381
00:32:33,577 --> 00:32:34,995
[sighs]

382
00:32:35,704 --> 00:32:38,248
Have that bastard and Chair Kim
confessed yet?

383
00:32:38,832 --> 00:32:40,250
We will make them.

384
00:32:40,334 --> 00:32:44,380
Do you actually think Chair Kim
killed someone over a painting?

385
00:32:44,463 --> 00:32:46,924
So far, she's the suspect
with the clearest motive.

386
00:32:47,007 --> 00:32:48,759
Even if she didn't do it herself,

387
00:32:48,842 --> 00:32:50,761
she could have ordered Ju Hyun-su.

388
00:32:50,844 --> 00:32:52,763
He was out of the country for a long time.

389
00:32:52,846 --> 00:32:55,683
And why would Chair Kim
mess with Han Seol-ah's men?

390
00:32:57,768 --> 00:33:01,480
You know, I still suspect Do Eun-hyuk,
but he has an alibi.

391
00:33:01,563 --> 00:33:03,565
[tense music playing]

392
00:33:05,067 --> 00:33:09,488
The CCTV footage shows that he was
at his studio in Cheongun

393
00:33:09,571 --> 00:33:11,240
when Paek Jun-beom was killed.

394
00:33:11,323 --> 00:33:12,616
Let me see that.

395
00:33:12,700 --> 00:33:14,702
You know I can't show you official files.

396
00:33:14,785 --> 00:33:17,204
Well, there were records seized
from Paek Jun-beom's house,

397
00:33:17,287 --> 00:33:19,164
of him stalking Han Seol-ah, right?

398
00:33:19,248 --> 00:33:20,833
Including the photos taken in Cheongun.

399
00:33:21,625 --> 00:33:22,626
[sighs]

400
00:33:24,753 --> 00:33:26,004
Could you, please?

401
00:33:26,088 --> 00:33:27,089
[sighs]

402
00:33:29,216 --> 00:33:31,218
[ominous music plays]

403
00:33:43,480 --> 00:33:47,568
[Gong] <i>The cell tower data shows that</i>
<i>Do Eun-hyuk was at his Cheongun studio</i>

404
00:33:47,651 --> 00:33:49,528
<i>when Paek Jun-beom was killed.</i>

405
00:33:52,948 --> 00:33:56,952
Now, I understand why
you trusted Cha Woo-seok.

406
00:33:59,121 --> 00:34:03,792
I never imagined someone
like Chair Kim could actually be arrested,

407
00:34:04,752 --> 00:34:08,338
and that's not something
I could've helped with.

408
00:34:09,381 --> 00:34:12,050
I figured that's why you joined
sides with Cha Woo-seok.

409
00:34:12,885 --> 00:34:14,052
No, not really.

410
00:34:14,720 --> 00:34:17,973
We both had things we had to do,
and somewhere along the way,

411
00:34:18,682 --> 00:34:20,768
we ended up having the same purpose,

412
00:34:22,478 --> 00:34:23,896
so we worked together.

413
00:34:26,815 --> 00:34:30,652
So it's a special connection.
Could it be fate?

414
00:34:32,321 --> 00:34:33,655
Tell me what do you think?

415
00:34:35,866 --> 00:34:37,367
You have a good eye for people.

416
00:34:38,869 --> 00:34:40,662
[gentle music playing]

417
00:34:44,500 --> 00:34:46,627
[gulps, sighs]

418
00:34:47,336 --> 00:34:49,505
He's a person who belongs
in the spotlight,

419
00:34:51,423 --> 00:34:53,342
confident and straightforward.

420
00:34:54,259 --> 00:34:55,427
I'm the opposite.

421
00:34:57,346 --> 00:34:59,515
Because I belong in the background.

422
00:35:02,893 --> 00:35:06,730
You see, I've been deliberately
ignoring this…

423
00:35:08,774 --> 00:35:10,609
but now I see it clearly.

424
00:35:12,236 --> 00:35:14,112
Why would you think that?

425
00:35:15,072 --> 00:35:17,241
[sighs] People…

426
00:35:19,284 --> 00:35:21,703
live according to what's ingrained
in them.

427
00:35:25,624 --> 00:35:27,876
Anyway, you've done a lot to get this far.

428
00:35:28,460 --> 00:35:29,545
Everything will be fine.

429
00:35:30,337 --> 00:35:33,173
I hope you get
Mr. Han's painting back too.

430
00:35:33,924 --> 00:35:35,717
I'm still on edge.

431
00:35:35,801 --> 00:35:39,263
You know, Chair Kim isn't the type
to go down quietly.

432
00:35:41,557 --> 00:35:42,558
Don't worry.

433
00:35:44,434 --> 00:35:46,520
It'll all work out the way you want.

434
00:35:58,949 --> 00:36:00,951
[ominous music plays]

435
00:36:26,935 --> 00:36:28,145
[knocks on door]

436
00:36:28,228 --> 00:36:30,856
Ms. Han, Chair Kim is here.

437
00:36:35,277 --> 00:36:38,697
They think there's no risk of escape,
for health reasons.

438
00:36:39,615 --> 00:36:40,908
It's always the same, you know?

439
00:36:40,991 --> 00:36:43,243
Damn, are these guys for real?

440
00:36:43,327 --> 00:36:44,995
She brought in a big law firm.

441
00:36:45,078 --> 00:36:46,747
Looks like their strategy worked.

442
00:36:46,830 --> 00:36:48,832
[liquid pouring]

443
00:36:52,753 --> 00:36:56,757
- [footsteps approaching]
- [slurps]

444
00:37:10,479 --> 00:37:11,647
Sit down.

445
00:37:20,072 --> 00:37:23,200
What's been going through your head
all this time, huh?

446
00:37:23,951 --> 00:37:27,579
Have you been living
with such determination

447
00:37:27,663 --> 00:37:29,539
to avenge your father?

448
00:37:31,083 --> 00:37:33,085
Well, I learned it all from you, ma'am.

449
00:37:33,168 --> 00:37:35,212
[scoffs]

450
00:37:39,132 --> 00:37:42,386
My father was a theater sign painter.

451
00:37:43,095 --> 00:37:45,514
I used to help him with painting,

452
00:37:45,597 --> 00:37:50,060
and then I became an apprentice
to become a real painter.

453
00:37:50,686 --> 00:37:53,563
But while watching your dad there,
I realized…

454
00:37:54,523 --> 00:37:55,691
[sighs]

455
00:37:56,191 --> 00:38:00,362
"Even a genius like him
can starve in this business."

456
00:38:01,863 --> 00:38:03,991
So you made him paint forgeries?

457
00:38:06,660 --> 00:38:11,415
It was to help him make a living,
so your family wouldn't starve to death.

458
00:38:11,498 --> 00:38:14,751
Hey, is it my fault that naive man

459
00:38:14,835 --> 00:38:17,129
took out loans
just so he could pay it all back?

460
00:38:17,713 --> 00:38:21,049
Do you really think that's, uh, an excuse
for causing his death?

461
00:38:21,133 --> 00:38:24,261
Who caused his death?
That was his own choice.

462
00:38:24,344 --> 00:38:28,682
I was the one who called 119
when your house caught fire.

463
00:38:28,765 --> 00:38:30,600
It was me! I saved you!

464
00:38:30,684 --> 00:38:32,978
You should've let me die back then!

465
00:38:35,147 --> 00:38:37,149
I wouldn't have suffered like this.

466
00:38:38,358 --> 00:38:40,777
Because I survived at the cost
of my parents' lives,

467
00:38:41,361 --> 00:38:43,864
I had to wag my tail like a dog
in front of you

468
00:38:43,947 --> 00:38:46,241
and smile until my mouth split.

469
00:38:48,910 --> 00:38:51,788
Even if you get away this time,

470
00:38:51,872 --> 00:38:54,374
I will hunt you down
to the ends of the Earth.

471
00:38:56,501 --> 00:38:57,502
[scoffs]

472
00:38:59,254 --> 00:39:00,756
What more can you do?

473
00:39:01,882 --> 00:39:04,801
The prosecutors and judges
are on my side anyway.

474
00:39:05,969 --> 00:39:09,514
You know, a dog might bite
its owner's hand once,

475
00:39:09,598 --> 00:39:13,769
but after that,
all it gets is beaten to death.

476
00:39:15,896 --> 00:39:18,315
So if I bite your neck,
it'll be the end of it.

477
00:39:19,316 --> 00:39:20,942
[chuckles]

478
00:39:22,027 --> 00:39:24,321
Do you think you'll even get the chance?

479
00:39:25,113 --> 00:39:28,450
Your neck will be the one on the line.

480
00:39:28,533 --> 00:39:30,869
[laughs]

481
00:39:33,455 --> 00:39:37,584
I guess we'll just have to wait and see…

482
00:39:40,212 --> 00:39:42,047
as to whose neck is on the line.

483
00:39:42,130 --> 00:39:44,424
[tense music playing]

484
00:40:08,865 --> 00:40:10,033
[screams]

485
00:40:12,911 --> 00:40:14,329
[breathes heavily]

486
00:40:22,462 --> 00:40:23,672
[line rings]

487
00:40:24,422 --> 00:40:26,341
Ju Hyun-su is getting out soon.

488
00:40:26,424 --> 00:40:28,677
Take care of that bastard quietly.

489
00:40:28,760 --> 00:40:29,761
If you fail,

490
00:40:31,388 --> 00:40:33,890
then that bitch is going
to learn the secret

491
00:40:33,974 --> 00:40:36,810
that you fear more than your own death.

492
00:40:38,520 --> 00:40:39,521
[line clicks]

493
00:41:08,466 --> 00:41:10,343
BOOKKEEPING LEDGER

494
00:41:18,977 --> 00:41:20,979
[soft guitar music playing]

495
00:41:29,112 --> 00:41:31,740
[humming]

496
00:41:34,993 --> 00:41:36,995
[singing in Spanish]

497
00:41:51,134 --> 00:41:53,136
[humming]

498
00:42:10,487 --> 00:42:12,489
[singing continues]

499
00:43:02,539 --> 00:43:04,541
NONGHYUP LIFE INSURANCE

500
00:43:32,444 --> 00:43:34,446
[mysterious music playing]

501
00:43:51,629 --> 00:43:54,215
[Woo-seok] <i>Something's off.</i>
<i>Everything's too perfect.</i>

502
00:44:05,518 --> 00:44:06,519
[sighs]

503
00:44:17,030 --> 00:44:18,156
Where are you going?

504
00:44:20,492 --> 00:44:21,534
Chair Kim's office.

505
00:44:22,118 --> 00:44:23,161
She called you?

506
00:44:23,912 --> 00:44:24,913
No.

507
00:44:26,498 --> 00:44:28,041
I'm going up to resign.

508
00:44:29,834 --> 00:44:31,920
Until the last auction… [sighs]

509
00:44:32,587 --> 00:44:35,465
…I wanted to take responsibility
for all the mess,

510
00:44:35,548 --> 00:44:38,051
- but Chair Kim…
- She wouldn't leave you alone.

511
00:44:38,635 --> 00:44:41,137
Let's go together. I'm quitting too.

512
00:44:42,013 --> 00:44:44,057
I told you, you didn't have to do that.

513
00:44:44,140 --> 00:44:49,396
I'd like to focus on my own work now.
And to get back in the water.

514
00:44:50,063 --> 00:44:53,066
[elevator dings, door opens]

515
00:45:13,044 --> 00:45:15,046
[record player scratching]

516
00:46:17,984 --> 00:46:20,361
[gasps]

517
00:46:20,445 --> 00:46:23,156
[screaming, gasping]

518
00:47:02,779 --> 00:47:05,907
According to the security guard,
he heard music playing all night long.

519
00:47:06,533 --> 00:47:08,743
Han Seol-ah and Do Eun-hyuk
were the first to find her.

520
00:47:08,826 --> 00:47:10,870
- Any foul play?
- Nothing yet.

521
00:47:11,454 --> 00:47:13,790
There's a suicide note on her laptop,

522
00:47:13,873 --> 00:47:16,334
but that's not enough
to conclude it was suicide.

523
00:47:16,417 --> 00:47:19,128
The CCTV around her office isn't working.

524
00:47:19,212 --> 00:47:20,547
[scoffs]

525
00:47:20,630 --> 00:47:23,591
She had to move the paintings
to her vault in secret.

526
00:47:23,675 --> 00:47:27,512
[sighs] In the end,
even her death became a secret.

527
00:47:33,893 --> 00:47:35,228
HAN SEOL-AH

528
00:47:35,311 --> 00:47:38,481
[voicemail] <i>The phone you are trying</i>
<i>to reach is turned off. You'll be direct--</i>

529
00:47:39,065 --> 00:47:41,067
[tires squealing]

530
00:48:27,196 --> 00:48:29,198
[doorbell rings]

531
00:48:46,633 --> 00:48:47,675
[sighs]

532
00:48:58,895 --> 00:49:01,689
This isn't the ending
that I was hoping for.

533
00:49:02,899 --> 00:49:05,526
Chair Kim would never kill herself.

534
00:49:05,610 --> 00:49:07,528
When I met her the day before,

535
00:49:07,612 --> 00:49:11,199
she still showed no guilt
and was completely confident.

536
00:49:12,492 --> 00:49:15,453
It looked like someone
had gone through her office.

537
00:49:17,789 --> 00:49:20,917
<i>It's strange that</i>
<i>she wrote the suicide note on her laptop.</i>

538
00:49:21,000 --> 00:49:24,379
She's the kind of person who still
keeps her ledgers written by hand.

539
00:49:28,633 --> 00:49:30,176
That means Chair Kim was also…

540
00:49:31,761 --> 00:49:33,179
It's all connected.

541
00:49:34,847 --> 00:49:36,474
For some reason,

542
00:49:37,100 --> 00:49:38,976
I think it's the work of one person.

543
00:49:39,852 --> 00:49:41,604
So until we catch the killer,

544
00:49:42,188 --> 00:49:43,731
nothing is over yet.

545
00:49:47,443 --> 00:49:48,444
[Woo-seok sighs]

546
00:49:52,115 --> 00:49:53,700
[Woo-seok gasps] Seol-ah.

547
00:49:54,826 --> 00:49:55,868
Are you okay?

548
00:49:57,328 --> 00:49:59,163
Wait, that's dangerous. I got it. Hold on.

549
00:50:26,232 --> 00:50:27,275
[Seung-jae] <i>Seol-ah,</i>

550
00:50:28,443 --> 00:50:31,654
<i>I hope the day never comes</i>
<i>where you have to read this.</i>

551
00:50:33,740 --> 00:50:37,952
<i>A woman came to see me</i>
<i>and said strange things about you.</i>

552
00:50:39,328 --> 00:50:41,330
<i>To be honest, it shook me.</i>

553
00:50:54,761 --> 00:50:57,180
This is Seung-jae's handwriting.

554
00:50:59,307 --> 00:51:01,309
He left a clue about the culprit.

555
00:51:03,811 --> 00:51:04,812
[gasps]

556
00:51:14,822 --> 00:51:17,658
- Are you okay?
- [gasping]

557
00:51:19,327 --> 00:51:20,328
Seol-ah.

558
00:51:22,413 --> 00:51:24,749
[sobbing, gasping]

559
00:51:46,604 --> 00:51:47,605
INSURANCE APPLICATION FORM

560
00:51:48,815 --> 00:51:50,900
INSURANCE AGENT: KIM MI-SUK

561
00:51:52,735 --> 00:51:53,778
[door closes]

562
00:51:57,573 --> 00:51:59,700
This is your parents'
life insurance policy.

563
00:52:01,828 --> 00:52:03,329
Check the agent's name for me.

564
00:52:05,331 --> 00:52:06,749
I think it might be someone you know.

565
00:52:06,833 --> 00:52:08,167
INSURANCE AGENT: KIM MI-SUK

566
00:52:22,640 --> 00:52:24,976
These photos were found
at Paek Jun-beom's house.

567
00:52:25,726 --> 00:52:29,021
I skimmed through them back then,
but there were some with Kim Yun-ji.

568
00:52:33,359 --> 00:52:37,488
That means she was in Cheongun
the day before Seung-jae died.

569
00:52:38,489 --> 00:52:39,866
Until the next morning.

570
00:52:43,286 --> 00:52:45,997
And this one here
was taken by the river that day.

571
00:52:55,298 --> 00:52:58,301
So, Kim Yun-ji was a witness, right?

572
00:52:59,927 --> 00:53:02,430
And she knew who murdered Seung-jae.

573
00:53:03,514 --> 00:53:05,141
That's why she was killed.

574
00:53:07,101 --> 00:53:08,102
[sighs]

575
00:53:09,604 --> 00:53:11,814
You think this could serve as evidence?

576
00:53:11,898 --> 00:53:15,776
Well, it may not be enough,
but the culprit will show up soon,

577
00:53:16,861 --> 00:53:20,281
because I'm with Han Seol-ah
and I know their secret.

578
00:53:21,365 --> 00:53:23,534
- If I don't take that chance--
- Oh, no.

579
00:53:23,618 --> 00:53:25,703
I'm not going to be using you as bait.

580
00:53:25,786 --> 00:53:29,498
I'm the only one who can get close
without raising suspicion.

581
00:53:29,582 --> 00:53:31,500
- I'll do it.
- It's too risky.

582
00:53:31,584 --> 00:53:32,752
Even Chair Kim is dead.

583
00:53:32,835 --> 00:53:37,048
What's dangerous is always living
with anxiety and in constant fear.

584
00:53:37,131 --> 00:53:38,883
I don't want to live like that anymore.

585
00:53:38,966 --> 00:53:40,384
Then let's go together.

586
00:53:40,468 --> 00:53:41,969
Together we'll get caught.

587
00:53:45,139 --> 00:53:48,267
Woo-seok, isn't there something
you need to look into?

588
00:53:49,435 --> 00:53:51,437
Let me know the route you're taking,

589
00:53:51,520 --> 00:53:53,272
and I'll keep you in the loop
about mine too.

590
00:53:56,984 --> 00:53:58,277
Be careful.

591
00:54:02,531 --> 00:54:04,450
- [door closes]
- [engine starts]

592
00:54:08,454 --> 00:54:11,332
[Gong] <i>You know,</i>
<i>I still suspect Do Eun-hyuk,</i>

593
00:54:11,415 --> 00:54:12,583
<i>but he has an alibi.</i>

594
00:54:12,667 --> 00:54:16,545
<i>The CCTV footage shows</i>
<i>that he was at his studio in Cheongun</i>

595
00:54:16,629 --> 00:54:18,255
<i>when Paek Jun-beom was killed.</i>

596
00:54:18,881 --> 00:54:22,009
["Fear Inside" playing]

597
00:54:50,454 --> 00:54:53,290
CHEONGUN STUDIO

598
00:54:54,875 --> 00:54:57,044
RECOMMENDED ROUTE
16 MINUTES

599
00:54:58,587 --> 00:55:00,631
If I step on the gas the whole way…

600
00:55:51,724 --> 00:55:53,934
BOOKKEEPING LEDGER

601
00:56:10,159 --> 00:56:12,411
BOOKKEEPING LEDGER

602
00:56:38,562 --> 00:56:40,773
DO EUN-HYUK

603
00:56:59,542 --> 00:57:01,001
[Woo-seok] <i>As long as the road is clear,</i>

604
00:57:01,085 --> 00:57:03,671
<i>it's possible to get</i>
<i>from Paek Jun-beom's villa</i>

605
00:57:03,754 --> 00:57:06,048
<i>to the studio in under 15 minutes.</i>

606
00:57:59,518 --> 00:58:01,896
PHOTO EQUIPMENT PURCHASE
LIVING EXPENSES

607
00:58:01,979 --> 00:58:03,564
DO EUN-HYE PRIVATE TUTORING EXPENSES

608
00:58:03,647 --> 00:58:04,773
LIVING EXPENSES

609
00:58:06,901 --> 00:58:08,527
EQUIPMENT PURCHASE

610
00:58:27,046 --> 00:58:29,423
DARKROOM & LARGE TANK INSTALLATION
SOUNDPROOFING WORK

611
00:59:43,289 --> 00:59:44,540
[hammer cocks]

612
00:59:50,921 --> 00:59:52,256
[Woo-seok] <i>I'm going to Cheongun.</i>

613
00:59:52,339 --> 00:59:54,425
CHA WOO-SEOK

614
01:00:00,389 --> 01:00:01,557
[Eun-hyuk] <i>Don't worry.</i>

615
01:00:02,933 --> 01:00:05,311
It'll all work out the way you want.

616
01:00:31,545 --> 01:00:32,838
Do Eun-hyuk.

617
01:01:18,509 --> 01:01:20,302
[Woo-seok] <i>If you fall in love</i>
<i>with Han Seol-ah,</i>

618
01:01:21,470 --> 01:01:22,596
<i>you will die.</i>

619
01:01:23,972 --> 01:01:25,557
[people shouting, screaming]

620
01:01:25,641 --> 01:01:27,559
I gained nothing at all.

621
01:01:27,643 --> 01:01:28,685
No!

622
01:01:28,769 --> 01:01:30,521
[Seol-ah] <i>I only lost.</i>

623
01:01:31,105 --> 01:01:33,148
[Woo-seok] <i>If the culprit</i>
<i>thinks I'm your boyfriend,</i>

624
01:01:33,732 --> 01:01:35,275
I'll end up dead,

625
01:01:36,402 --> 01:01:38,070
<i>or I'll find out who the killer is.</i>

626
01:01:38,153 --> 01:01:40,030
What if you really end up dead?

627
01:01:40,114 --> 01:01:42,616
[Woo-seok] <i>I said I don't care.</i>
<i>You can use me.</i>

628
01:01:43,575 --> 01:01:45,577
- [Seol-ah] <i>So until we catch the killer…</i>
- [screams]

629
01:01:46,829 --> 01:01:48,497
…nothing is over yet.

630
01:01:48,580 --> 01:01:50,499
[Woo-seok] <i>But the culprit</i>
<i>will show up soon,</i>

631
01:01:50,582 --> 01:01:51,834
<i>because I'm with Han Seol-ah…</i>

632
01:01:51,917 --> 01:01:53,919
- [grunts]
- <i>…and I know their secret.</i>
